### ============================================
### VERIFICATION CHECKLIST
### ============================================
### 
### ✅ CreatedAt Field:
### - [ ] CreatedAt is set automatically when message is created
### - [ ] CreatedAt is NOT NULL
### - [ ] CreatedAt uses UTC timezone
### - [ ] CreatedAt is before or equal to current time
### 
### ✅ ProcessedAt Field:
### - [ ] ProcessedAt is NULL when message is first created
### - [ ] ProcessedAt remains NULL while message is unprocessed
### - [ ] ProcessedAt is set after background job processes message (if using soft delete)
### - [ ] ProcessedAt is after CreatedAt
### 
### ✅ Query Performance:
### - [ ] Can filter by ProcessedAt == null efficiently
### - [ ] Can order by CreatedAt
### - [ ] Index on CreatedAt improves query speed
### - [ ] Index on ProcessedAt improves query speed
### 
### ✅ Monitoring:
### - [ ] Can see total message count
### - [ ] Can see unprocessed vs processed count
### - [ ] Can see oldest unprocessed message
### - [ ] Can calculate processing time (ProcessedAt - CreatedAt)

### ============================================
### NOTES
### ============================================
### 
### CURRENT BEHAVIOR (Hard Delete):
### - Message is created with CreatedAt = NOW, ProcessedAt = NULL
### - Background job reads messages where ProcessedAt == NULL
### - After successful publish, message is DELETED from database
### - ProcessedAt is never set (because message is deleted)
### 
### ALTERNATIVE BEHAVIOR (Soft Delete):
### - Message is created with CreatedAt = NOW, ProcessedAt = NULL
### - Background job reads messages where ProcessedAt == NULL
### - After successful publish, message.MarkAsProcessed() sets ProcessedAt = NOW
### - Message stays in database for audit/monitoring
### - Cleanup job can delete old processed messages later
### 
### TO SWITCH TO SOFT DELETE:
### Modify Outbox.DeleteMessageAsync() to use MarkAsProcessed() instead of ExecuteDeleteAsync()
